    "Self-formation, then, and counter-conduct in particular, are deeply connected with the ethical subject (Davidson 2011; Engels 2019).",
    "It appears that insofar as they reinvent themselves in relation to themselves and others, self-conducting subjects are moral subjects.",
    "That is not to say good or bad, but precisely the kind of agents that can make moral decisions.",
    "In an unusually succinct reply to an interview question, Foucault said that \"[f]reedom is the ontological condition of ethics.",
    "But ethics is the considered form that freedom takes when it is informed by reflection\"."
  ],
